== English ==
{{wikipedia}}

=== Etymology ===
From "Damn the torpedoes, full speed ahead!", a famous order issued by Admiral [[w:David Farragut|David Farragut]] during the [[w:Battle of Mobile Bay|Battle of Mobile Bay]].

=== Phrase ===
'''damn the torpedoes'''
# {{idiom}} to [[heroic]]ally [[dismiss]] the [[consequence]]s of a [[dangerous]] or [[inadvisable]] action
#* ''Straight ahead, take no prisoners, and damn the torpedoes!''
#* ''Just fake it, and damn the torpedoes if anyone notices.''